The 2019-20 coronavirus pandemic is an ongoing pandemic of 2019 coronavirus disease (COVID-19), caused by SARS-CoV-2.
The outbreak in Wuhan, China, was identified in December 2019, declared an international public health emergency of concern on January 30, 2020, and recognized as a pandemic on March 11, 2020.
As of 10 April 2020, approximately 1.61 million cases of COVID-19 have been reported in 210 countries and territories, resulting in approximately 97,000 deaths.
