Authorities around the world are responding to this threat by imposing travel restrictions, quarantines, curfews, workplace risk controls and closures.
The pandemic has led to severe global social and economic disruption, postponement or cancellation of sporting, religious, political, and cultural events, and widespread shortages of supplies exacerbated by purchasing panic.
Schools and universities have closed either nationally or locally in 193 countries, affecting about 99.4 percent of the world’s students.
