Cases are mostly related to the Wuhan Seafood Wholesale Market, so the virus is believed to be of animal origin.
The virus that caused the outbreak is known as SARS-CoV-2, a newly discovered virus that is closely related to coronaviruses in bats, coronaviruses in squamous ant-eaters, and SARS-CoV. It was later discovered that the first person with symptoms had been contacted with a group of this person on 1 December 2019.
Of the group of early cases reported in December 2019, two-thirds were found to be market-related.
