About 80% of deaths in China as of 5 February were concentrated in people over 60 years of age, and 75% had pre-existing conditions including cardiovascular disease and diabetes. Official statistics of COVID-19 deaths generally refer to those who have been confirmed to have been infected with COVID according to official protocols.
